# 🔥 Kiln — Fire Your Listings

AI-powered Etsy listing generator for print-on-demand sellers. Connect your Etsy shop, let Claude generate optimized titles, descriptions, and tags from your draft listings, then push them back in one click.

---

## Setup

### 1. Clone & install dependencies

```bash
# Backend
cd server
npm install

# Frontend
cd ../client
npm install
```

### 2. Configure environment

```bash
cd server
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` and fill in:

| Variable | Where to get it |
|---|---|
| `ETSY_API_KEY` | [etsy.com/developers](https://www.etsy.com/developers) → your app → Keystring |
| `ETSY_API_SECRET` | Same page → Shared Secret |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | [console.anthropic.com](https://console.anthropic.com) |
| `SESSION_SECRET` | Any random string |

> **Etsy Callback URL:** When registering your app on Etsy, set the callback URL to:
> `http://localhost:3001/auth/etsy/callback`

### 3. Run the app

Open two terminals:

```bash
# Terminal 1 — Backend
cd server
npm run dev

# Terminal 2 — Frontend
cd client
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) in your browser.

---

## How It Works

1. **Connect** your Etsy shop via OAuth
2. **View** all your draft listings in the queue
3. **Select** a product template (optional but recommended)
4. **Generate** — Claude reads the listing title, category, price, and photos and writes a full listing
5. **Review & edit** the generated title, description, and tags
6. **Push** back to Etsy with one click

---

## Templates

Templates let you define a consistent description structure per product type (mugs, shirts, totes, etc.) with `[PLACEHOLDERS]` that Claude fills in based on the specific design.

Templates are stored in your browser's localStorage — no server storage needed for the MVP.

---

## Project Structure

```
kiln/
├── server/
│   ├── index.js        # Express server, Etsy OAuth, Claude API
│   ├── .env.example    # Environment template
│   └── package.json
└── client/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── App.jsx
    │   ├── components/
    │   │   ├── Layout.jsx
    │   │   └── ListingCard.jsx
    │   └── pages/
    │       ├── ConnectPage.jsx
    │       ├── DashboardPage.jsx
    │       └── TemplatesPage.jsx
    ├── index.html
    ├── vite.config.js
    └── package.json
```

